task.summary: Default task
New branch for layout
Skinning kind of works??? It breaks everything but is definitely doing something.
Images was in the wrong folder -- it's working?!
Moved the styling call to a separate function, and began to add padding and make fonts more readable -- not done, but it's started.
Changes to match the demo more closely. Layout changes still needed, as well as updates to the controller bitmaps.
Edited the formatting of the individual lower panel tab pane object as an example.
Extra commit -- Edited the formatting of the individual lower panel tab pane object as an example.
Added new button images

Moved what settings I could into the theme.xml file. Moved layout related things into a layout module. Created a .json file for storing color settings. Added a json reading library (open source). Wrote a singleton to store the color settings -- can be extended to read more than just color related settings fairly easily.
Added documentation for layout/SettingsAccessor.java. Also pushing my workspace.xml file in hopes of it making the GSON library work for others.
Moved GSON library into a place that will hopefully work for others. Slightly edited SettingsAccessor.java.
Added the sidebar. Currently only controls the "bottom part" of the screen, excluding the top bar, but I think that can be changed relatively easily.

Sidebar now fully contains the previously-written model view! Additionally, it provides an easy method which adds a tab to the left-sidebar so that we can extend the program to include analytics and map views. The WPI Logo has also been added to the top of the left-sidebar.
Changes to formatting and future-proofing sizing in LeftSideBar.
Settings are far more versatile now. Began on analytics view.
Up to date JSONReader class and addition of JFreeChart library.

Rudimentary Analytics View Added
Also:
- Analytics branch created - Significant changes to JSONReader - Restructuring of LeftSideBar to inherit from a new SideBar class - Addition __but not use__ of a View interface. This will be used in the future.

Fixed resize issue with MainWindow.
Also in process of making graphs more customizable.

Graphs are significantly more customizable.
Each graph has an entry in src/edu/usfca/vas/analytics/analyticsSettings.json which can optionally specify a wide range of settings such as title, labels, and colors.
Created preprocessor in python. The output was successful!
Removed clutter
